

f(z) = sigma(z) = 1/(1+e^(-z))

f'(z) = f(z) * (1-f(z)) ---  for gradient , for backpropagation , loss (basically for checing the error / diff in actual vs expected value)

 op = (0,1) (not included)
useful for binary classification -- spam/not spam, 

disadv --  suffers gradient vanishing problem (slow learning)

how slow  learning -- as -- if z is too high or small -- then derivative is too small -- so this leads to not proper training of the weights
